22/04/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Bucharest Institute for Infectious Diseases has found several people showing symptoms of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS). 
Institute Director Adrian Streinu Cercel confirmed that, in at least one case, tests proved positive. 
The institute has increased controls to reduce the risks of contagion. 
In Croatia, the Public Health Institute reported Monday there are no cases of SARS in the country. 
(Ziua - 22/04/03; bTV, HINA - 21/04/03)
